
Conditional Rendering


Conditional Rendering
• Conditional rendering allows components to display UI based 
on conditions or state value.
• This allows you to dynamically control what content is 
displayed to the user based on the state of your application. 
• This can be done using several methods, such as JavaScript's 
conditional operators (if-else, ternary operator) or logical 
operators like && and ||.
